WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:0
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:03.650
Wealth, fame, power...

3
00:00:03.650 --> 00:00:07.820
Gold Roger, the King of the Pirates, obtained everything the world has to offer.

4
00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.660
What he said in his final moments drove countless souls to the seas.

5
00:00:11.660 --> 00:00:13.660
You want my treasure?

6
00:00:13.660 --> 00:00:15.450
Go ahead.

7
00:00:15.450 --> 00:00:16.660
Find it!

8
00:00:16.660 --> 00:00:19.250
Everything is right where I left it!

9
00:00:21.670 --> 00:00:26.380
People set their sights on the Grand Line in pursuit of their dreams.

10
00:00:26.380 --> 00:00:29.630
The world has truly entered the Great Pirate Era!

11
00:00:30.390 --> 00:00:35.640
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams

12
00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:35.640
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

13
00:00:35.850 --> 00:00:41.440
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

14
00:00:41.770 --> 00:00:42.690
One Piece!
ONE PIECE

15
00:00:47.900 --> 00:00:52.700
Compasses? Not for me. Left them all behind
Rashinban nante juutai no moto

16
00:00:53.580 --> 00:00:58.500
I'm headed out to sea, with my heart serving as guide
Netsu ni ukasare kaji wo toru no sa

17
00:00:59.330 --> 00:01:04.540
Following the ancient map to the spot marked "X" reveals
Hokori kabutteta takara no chizu mo

18
00:01:04.540 --> 00:01:09.760
Yeah, it's only legendary till someone proves it's real
Tashikameta no nara densetsu janai!

19
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:13.710
When the world's got you down,

20
00:01:11.380 --> 00:01:16.850
Kojin teki na arashi wa dare ka no

21
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:16.850
lean on your crew, they'll turn it around

22
00:01:17.180 --> 00:01:22.190
Their biorhythm will carry you through
BIORHYTHM nokkatte

23
00:01:22.400 --> 00:01:24.230
We're gonna make the most of it
Omoi sugoseba ii!

24
00:01:26.110 --> 00:01:31.400
Come aboard and bring along all your hopes and dreams
Arittake no yume wo kaki atsume

25
00:01:31.610 --> 00:01:36.990
I know together we'll find everything we're looking for
Sagashi mono wo sagashi ni yuku no sa

26
00:01:37.330 --> 00:01:40.040
Got some change to my name,
POCKET no COIN

27
00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.250
and maybe you wanna be my friend?
Soreto YOU WANNA BE MY FRIEND?

28
00:01:43.540 --> 00:01:48.130
We are, we are on the cruise!
WE ARE, WE ARE ON THE CRUISE!

29
00:01:48.920 --> 00:01:49.760
WE ARE!

30
00:01:50.010 --> 00:01:53.220
Townsfolks'
Emergency Shelter

31
00:01:53.220 --> 00:01:54.550
This is strange...

32
00:01:54.550 --> 00:01:57.680
The mayor usually isn't
gone for so long...

33
00:01:57.680 --> 00:02:00.390
Something must have
happened in town!

34
00:02:00.390 --> 00:02:03.900
Also, there's been more
cannon fire than usual!

35
00:02:03.900 --> 00:02:07.320
Alright, I'll go check out
the town. You all stay here!

36
00:02:07.320 --> 00:02:08.520
I'm coming too!

37
00:02:08.520 --> 00:02:09.860
Don't be an idiot!

38
00:02:09.860 --> 00:02:13.360
Those wretched
Buggy Pirates are in town!

39
00:02:13.360 --> 00:02:15.910
Exactly! I'm coming too!

40
00:02:15.910 --> 00:02:20.660
What kind of citizens are we if we
can't even keep our mayor safe?!

41
00:02:20.660 --> 00:02:22.410
It's no use trying to stop us!

42
00:02:22.410 --> 00:02:24.790
This is all of our own accord!

43
00:02:26.330 --> 00:02:27.590
Fine. Do what you want.

44
00:02:27.590 --> 00:02:28.920
Let's go, everyone!

45
00:02:28.920 --> 00:02:32.130
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

46
00:02:35.260 --> 00:02:40.720
Pirate Buggy "the Clown"

47
00:02:35.970 --> 00:02:40.560
Never in my life has anyone
made me angrier than he did!

48
00:02:40.560 --> 00:02:44.940
Thanks to that bastard Shanks,
I missed out on the score of a lifetime!

49
00:02:44.940 --> 00:02:47.480
I don't know how you two
are connected,

50
00:02:47.480 --> 00:02:50.190
but I'll say whatever
I want about him!

51
00:02:54.360 --> 00:02:56.660
– Get him! Get him! Fight!
– Stand your ground, you two!

52
00:02:56.660 --> 00:02:57.530
The North Pole!

53
00:02:57.530 --> 00:02:58.410
No, the South Pole!

54
00:02:58.410 --> 00:02:59.410
You won't budge, huh?!

55
00:02:59.410 --> 00:03:02.370
You got it! And I'll keep
sayin' it 'cause I'm right!

56
00:03:02.750 --> 00:03:05.710
Oh, you've got guts!
Let's settle this once and for all!

57
00:03:05.710 --> 00:03:07.130
Go ahead and try it!

58
00:03:07.130 --> 00:03:10.340
Alright, you bastard!
You're in for a flashy beatdown!

59
00:03:10.340 --> 00:03:11.170
You wish!

60
00:03:11.170 --> 00:03:12.340
Knock it off!

61
00:03:13.130 --> 00:03:16.050
Who cares whether it's colder
at the South or North Pole?!

62
00:03:16.380 --> 00:03:19.850
If you wanna know that badly,
go to both and find out!

63
00:03:19.850 --> 00:03:21.060
Now cool it!

64
00:03:21.060 --> 00:03:22.970
A ship!

65
00:03:22.970 --> 00:03:25.770
Enemy ship to the north-northeast!

66
00:03:25.770 --> 00:03:28.520
Alright, get ready! Time to fight!

67
00:03:28.520 --> 00:03:29.770
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

68
00:03:29.770 --> 00:03:32.150
Great! I'm gonna plunder up a storm!

69
00:03:32.150 --> 00:03:33.820
You sure seem happy, Buggy!

70
00:03:33.820 --> 00:03:34.610
Obviously!

71
00:03:35.030 --> 00:03:37.780
Enemy ships are like treasure chests.

72
00:03:37.780 --> 00:03:39.410
Pirates love to crack 'em open!

73
00:03:39.410 --> 00:03:40.490
Am I wrong?!

74
00:03:41.160 --> 00:03:42.910
Well, there is some truth to that.

75
00:03:42.910 --> 00:03:44.160
You're too soft!

76
00:03:44.160 --> 00:03:48.750
You and everyone else here
never talk seriously about treasure!

77
00:03:49.080 --> 00:03:51.290
You don't know what
it means to be a pirate!

78
00:03:59.050 --> 00:04:01.010
Wh-What's this?!

79
00:04:01.010 --> 00:04:03.680
A... A... A treasure map!

80
00:04:04.310 --> 00:04:07.640
I've never seen one before! Awesome!

81
00:04:08.640 --> 00:04:11.520
It's just sitting there on
the bottom of the ocean?

82
00:04:13.980 --> 00:04:20.820
Yes! My path has been set
in the flashiest of ways!

83
00:04:27.960 --> 00:04:30.580
Today was another easy win!

84
00:04:30.580 --> 00:04:32.170
Hey! Drink up!

85
00:04:32.170 --> 00:04:33.250
Hey, Buggy!

86
00:04:33.250 --> 00:04:35.170
You're not gonna party with us?

87
00:04:35.170 --> 00:04:37.090
The loot today was really something!

88
00:04:37.090 --> 00:04:40.050
I-I ain't got nothin',
and I don't know nothin'!

89
00:04:40.050 --> 00:04:42.800
Huh? What are you talking about?

90
00:04:42.800 --> 00:04:44.260
Oh, uh...

91
00:04:48.060 --> 00:04:51.940
You said you were gonna
leave this ship someday.

92
00:04:51.940 --> 00:04:53.940
Got any big plans?

93
00:04:53.940 --> 00:04:55.730
I'm gonna have my own ship.

94
00:04:55.730 --> 00:04:59.240
I'll gather a reliable crew
and then see the world.

95
00:04:59.240 --> 00:05:03.120
It'll be at a nice, leisurely pace,
and as a pirate, of course.

96
00:05:03.120 --> 00:05:06.160
You always spout that sentimental crap.

97
00:05:06.160 --> 00:05:07.120
I do?

98
00:05:07.120 --> 00:05:10.250
I can't deny you're good in a fight,

99
00:05:10.250 --> 00:05:14.210
but if you were a bit more ruthless,
I may have let you be my henchman.

100
00:05:14.210 --> 00:05:16.630
Me? One of your
henchmen? Get real!

101
00:05:16.630 --> 00:05:17.210
Huh?

102
00:05:18.510 --> 00:05:20.220
Our outlooks are too different,

103
00:05:20.220 --> 00:05:22.970
so we should just go
our separate ways.

104
00:05:22.970 --> 00:05:24.050
As pirates do.

105
00:05:25.050 --> 00:05:27.430
Who made you
the expert on pirates, huh?

106
00:05:27.430 --> 00:05:30.890
And if we ever cross prows,
we'll need to cross swords.

107
00:05:31.520 --> 00:05:33.980
Yeah... As pirates do...

108
00:05:34.520 --> 00:05:36.320
I don't get you sometimes...

109
00:05:37.280 --> 00:05:40.780
Anyway, you said
something about loot...

110
00:05:40.780 --> 00:05:42.910
Yeah, we found a devil fruit.

111
00:05:42.910 --> 00:05:43.990
Devil fruit?

112
00:05:44.320 --> 00:05:47.740
I heard they're
incarnations of sea devils.

113
00:05:47.740 --> 00:05:50.000
They say eating one
grants a devil's powers,

114
00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:53.670
but the sea will hate you
and make you sink like an anchor.

115
00:05:53.670 --> 00:05:56.290
You'd have to be stupid
to eat something like that!

116
00:05:56.960 --> 00:06:01.970
I'd never get all that treasure
on the ocean floor if I couldn't swim!

117
00:06:01.970 --> 00:06:02.930
You know,

118
00:06:03.380 --> 00:06:06.640
it would easily sell
for 100 million berries...

119
00:06:08.930 --> 00:06:09.720
What?!

120
00:06:10.980 --> 00:06:15.060
I, pirate apprentice Buggy,
will now eat this devil fruit!

121
00:06:16.310 --> 00:06:19.480
Gotta love kids, never thinking
of the consequences...

122
00:06:21.360 --> 00:06:24.820
– Whoa!
– He ate it!

123
00:06:24.820 --> 00:06:25.990
Well, Buggy?

124
00:06:25.990 --> 00:06:27.870
Anything different about your body?

125
00:06:27.870 --> 00:06:29.620
No... Not really...

126
00:06:29.620 --> 00:06:31.200
So, what? Was it fake?

127
00:06:31.870 --> 00:06:36.040
Not surprising. I've only heard
about devil fruits from rumors.

128
00:06:38.250 --> 00:06:41.260
Yes! What a flashy success!

129
00:06:41.260 --> 00:06:44.130
What I ate this afternoon
was a fake I made!

130
00:06:44.130 --> 00:06:46.590
I can't believe everything
went so smoothly!

131
00:06:46.590 --> 00:06:49.640
Now to jump ship
before they find out the truth!

132
00:06:49.640 --> 00:06:52.770
If I sell the devil fruit
and the map's treasure,

133
00:06:52.770 --> 00:06:55.850
I'll have enough money to form
my own pirate crew right away!

134
00:06:56.400 --> 00:06:57.650
Hey, Buggy!

135
00:06:57.650 --> 00:06:59.400
Whatcha grinning about?

136
00:06:59.400 --> 00:07:01.900
Oh, it's you...
Don't scare me like that.

137
00:07:01.900 --> 00:07:03.690
What kind of face is that?

138
00:07:04.320 --> 00:07:07.660
Keep stealing from the kitchen,
and the cook will give you hell!

139
00:07:08.530 --> 00:07:10.160
Whew, that was close...

140
00:07:10.160 --> 00:07:11.490
Oh, that reminds me!

141
00:07:11.490 --> 00:07:12.750
The captain just–

142
00:07:18.920 --> 00:07:21.170
– What the...?!
– Shanks! Damn you!

143
00:07:21.170 --> 00:07:23.670
My... My... I'm...

144
00:07:24.550 --> 00:07:26.180
What's that scrap of paper?

145
00:07:26.800 --> 00:07:27.930
My map!

146
00:07:29.050 --> 00:07:30.890
Hey, Buggy!

147
00:07:32.720 --> 00:07:35.690
What gives? I can't move...

148
00:07:36.230 --> 00:07:39.360
So then it's true that you
sink like an anchor?!

149
00:07:39.360 --> 00:07:40.650
Crap!

150
00:07:41.070 --> 00:07:42.980
Hey! Buggy! What are you doing?

151
00:07:42.980 --> 00:07:44.650
You're great at swimming!

152
00:07:47.820 --> 00:07:48.780
Buggy!

153
00:07:49.740 --> 00:07:52.740
H-Help me...

154
00:07:52.740 --> 00:07:57.710
I'll save you, Buggy!

155
00:08:05.090 --> 00:08:07.800
So Shanks saved you?

156
00:08:07.800 --> 00:08:10.010
That's not what I'm trying to say!

157
00:08:10.640 --> 00:08:15.180
Because of him, my life's ambitions
were put on hold for ten years!

158
00:08:15.600 --> 00:08:17.310
And then I had a revelation!

159
00:08:17.310 --> 00:08:21.150
If below the sea is off limits,
I'll obtain all the treasure above land...

160
00:08:21.650 --> 00:08:24.900
using this Chop-Chop power.

161
00:08:24.900 --> 00:08:32.530
That's why I won't let anyone
who touches my treasure live!

162
00:08:34.450 --> 00:08:36.620
Let go...

163
00:08:36.620 --> 00:08:38.960
of my treasure!

164
00:08:38.960 --> 00:08:40.750
Crap! He spotted me!

165
00:08:42.670 --> 00:08:45.630
Don't think you can escape me, Nami!

166
00:08:46.130 --> 00:08:48.630
I'm going to flashily
slice you to pieces!

167
00:08:59.890 --> 00:09:01.190
Balls...

168
00:09:02.020 --> 00:09:06.480
R-Right... i-i-i-in... the balls...

169
00:09:07.110 --> 00:09:09.450
You're still dealing with me!

170
00:09:10.320 --> 00:09:11.360
Hey!

171
00:09:12.110 --> 00:09:14.330
Leave that treasure
and get out of here!

172
00:09:14.330 --> 00:09:15.580
He'll just keep coming.

173
00:09:15.580 --> 00:09:16.330
No!

174
00:09:16.740 --> 00:09:18.910
Leave the treasure
and get out of here?!

175
00:09:18.910 --> 00:09:19.910
Absolutely not!

176
00:09:19.910 --> 00:09:22.670
Why should I leave
my treasure behind?!

177
00:09:23.380 --> 00:09:25.460
Your treasure?!

178
00:09:25.460 --> 00:09:27.210
Of course it is!

179
00:09:27.210 --> 00:09:29.220
I'm a thief who only
steals from pirates,

180
00:09:29.220 --> 00:09:31.430
and I just stole from a pirate!

181
00:09:32.430 --> 00:09:36.260
Meaning, this treasure
now belongs to me!

182
00:09:36.260 --> 00:09:38.430
Ah, I see!

183
00:09:38.430 --> 00:09:40.270
My ass, it is!

184
00:09:40.270 --> 00:09:41.690
That's my treasure!

185
00:09:41.690 --> 00:09:44.310
Do you think stealing it
makes it yours?!

186
00:09:45.480 --> 00:09:48.730
Honestly! What kind of
upbringing did you have?!

187
00:09:48.730 --> 00:09:51.610
A criminal, trying to lecture
another criminal?

188
00:09:51.610 --> 00:09:52.660
That's rich!

189
00:09:52.660 --> 00:09:53.610
What?!

190
00:09:53.950 --> 00:09:59.040
I haven't fallen so low that I need
to be lectured by pirates!

191
00:10:01.710 --> 00:10:05.080
I hope you're ready to face
the consequences, Nami...

192
00:10:05.080 --> 00:10:09.260
Chop-Chop...

193
00:10:09.260 --> 00:10:12.760
Festival!

194
00:10:15.300 --> 00:10:19.220
Just try and help your friend
if you can, Gum-Gum!

195
00:10:19.220 --> 00:10:22.770
Damn, he's split apart even more!

196
00:10:24.310 --> 00:10:25.520
What's this?

197
00:10:25.900 --> 00:10:26.690
Nami!

198
00:10:27.860 --> 00:10:30.230
Give me my back my treasure!

199
00:10:29.150 --> 00:10:30.230
You wish!

200
00:10:32.950 --> 00:10:34.950
Coochie, coochie, coo!

201
00:10:40.660 --> 00:10:42.330
Damn, you're stubborn!

202
00:10:44.580 --> 00:10:46.290
Knock it off!

203
00:10:46.290 --> 00:10:50.170
No, you knock it off!

204
00:10:55.590 --> 00:10:57.930
Thanks for returning the treasure!

205
00:10:59.600 --> 00:11:04.440
Let go! Let go! That's mine!

206
00:11:00.310 --> 00:11:04.440
Let go?! This is my treasure!

207
00:11:04.440 --> 00:11:06.020
You let go!

208
00:11:09.020 --> 00:11:11.820
Die!

209
00:11:12.650 --> 00:11:16.410
I told you, you're dealing with me!

210
00:11:42.220 --> 00:11:45.430
That big kick just now was
for the old mayor guy!

211
00:11:47.770 --> 00:11:49.730
Thanks for saving me.

212
00:11:49.730 --> 00:11:51.570
Yeah, no problem!

213
00:11:52.020 --> 00:11:53.980
Oh yeah! The map!

214
00:11:52.610 --> 00:11:53.980
My treasure–

215
00:11:54.360 --> 00:11:57.950
This isn't over yet, Gum-Gum!

216
00:11:57.950 --> 00:11:59.070
He's still alive!

217
00:11:59.070 --> 00:12:00.450
Shut up!

218
00:12:00.450 --> 00:12:03.910
How dare you flashily do this to me!

219
00:12:03.910 --> 00:12:06.210
You'll pay for this!

220
00:12:07.210 --> 00:12:09.710
Assemble! Chop-Chop Parts!

221
00:12:17.300 --> 00:12:18.840
Huh?

222
00:12:21.350 --> 00:12:22.680
Looking for these?!

223
00:12:23.560 --> 00:12:25.140
My parts!

224
00:12:26.060 --> 00:12:28.640
Way to go, thief!

225
00:12:28.640 --> 00:12:30.310
D-D-Don't!

226
00:12:30.310 --> 00:12:32.190
Beat it, Buggy!

227
00:12:32.190 --> 00:12:34.280
Gum-Gum...

228
00:12:35.400 --> 00:12:37.280
Bazooka!

229
00:12:49.210 --> 00:12:50.540
I win!

230
00:12:52.630 --> 00:12:56.130
Hey! Captain Buggy went flying!

231
00:12:56.130 --> 00:12:59.170
Wh-What do we do?!

232
00:12:59.170 --> 00:13:00.760
Play dead for now!

233
00:13:00.760 --> 00:13:01.640
Good idea!

234
00:13:07.100 --> 00:13:09.140
It's all torn up now...

235
00:13:09.140 --> 00:13:10.640
Well, that's okay!

236
00:13:10.640 --> 00:13:14.570
I can still put it on, plus I sent
Buggy flying, so I'm happy.

237
00:13:19.570 --> 00:13:21.030
It's all right.

238
00:13:21.030 --> 00:13:22.780
I'll fix it for you later.

239
00:13:22.780 --> 00:13:24.120
Huh? What?

240
00:13:24.120 --> 00:13:25.740
Nothing!

241
00:13:25.740 --> 00:13:29.120
So anyway, I split it into
two bags, so carry half of it!

242
00:13:29.120 --> 00:13:31.370
It's too heavy for me!

243
00:13:31.370 --> 00:13:32.540
There sure is a lot!

244
00:13:32.920 --> 00:13:37.380
If nothing else, Buggy does know
quality treasure when he sees it!

245
00:13:37.380 --> 00:13:40.880
This has to be worth
at least 10 million berries!

246
00:13:45.180 --> 00:13:46.720
Here you go.

247
00:13:46.720 --> 00:13:47.470
Huh?

248
00:13:47.470 --> 00:13:49.350
It's a map to the Grand Line.

249
00:13:49.350 --> 00:13:50.480
You want it, right?

250
00:13:50.480 --> 00:13:51.480
I can have it?!

251
00:13:51.480 --> 00:13:53.060
You did save me.

252
00:13:53.810 --> 00:13:55.440
Thanks, Nami!

253
00:13:55.440 --> 00:13:58.690
I finally got a map to the Grand Line!

254
00:13:58.690 --> 00:14:00.190
Hooray!

255
00:14:00.570 --> 00:14:03.570
Oh! Does that mean
you'll join our crew now?!

256
00:14:03.570 --> 00:14:07.030
I told you I'm never
going to join a pirate crew!

257
00:14:08.200 --> 00:14:09.330
But okay!

258
00:14:09.330 --> 00:14:12.040
Staying with you guys
seems profitable enough.

259
00:14:12.040 --> 00:14:14.920
But let me be clear;
we're just teaming up.

260
00:14:14.920 --> 00:14:16.340
Don't forget that!

261
00:14:16.340 --> 00:14:17.460
Yeah!

262
00:14:20.340 --> 00:14:22.630
Hey, Zoro! Wake up!

263
00:14:22.630 --> 00:14:24.890
Zoro! We're going!

264
00:14:26.600 --> 00:14:28.350
Did we take care of everything?

265
00:14:27.600 --> 00:14:28.350
Yeah!

266
00:14:28.350 --> 00:14:31.520
We also got the map,
some treasure, and a navigator!

267
00:14:36.440 --> 00:14:38.190
No good... Out of blood...

268
00:14:38.190 --> 00:14:39.440
I don't think I can walk.

269
00:14:39.440 --> 00:14:40.610
You think?!

270
00:14:40.610 --> 00:14:43.820
It's not even human for either
of you to be walking after that!

271
00:14:43.820 --> 00:14:45.450
Wait, why me too?

272
00:14:45.450 --> 00:14:47.780
You're even less human than he is!

273
00:14:47.780 --> 00:14:50.290
Anyway, let's help the mayor.

274
00:14:50.290 --> 00:14:51.410
Oh, yeah!

275
00:14:52.160 --> 00:14:54.330
We gotta wake up
the old mayor guy now.

276
00:14:54.330 --> 00:14:55.370
You, there!

277
00:14:55.870 --> 00:14:57.500
Are you outsiders?!

278
00:14:57.500 --> 00:14:59.500
Yeah. Who are you?

279
00:15:00.050 --> 00:15:02.510
We're the citizens of this town!

280
00:15:02.510 --> 00:15:04.380
Did the pirates have a falling out?!

281
00:15:05.800 --> 00:15:07.800
If you know anything, tell us!

282
00:15:07.800 --> 00:15:10.430
Oh, it's just the citizens!

283
00:15:10.430 --> 00:15:12.140
I was scared it was more pirates.

284
00:15:12.140 --> 00:15:13.270
Oh, Mayor!

285
00:15:13.270 --> 00:15:15.060
Oh no! Say something!

286
00:15:15.060 --> 00:15:16.150
Hey, Mayor!

287
00:15:16.150 --> 00:15:18.230
– He's out cold!
– This had to be the pirates!

288
00:15:18.230 --> 00:15:20.270
How horrible!

289
00:15:20.270 --> 00:15:21.150
Sorry.

290
00:15:21.150 --> 00:15:23.190
I had to knock out the old man.

291
00:15:23.190 --> 00:15:24.610
– What?!
– What?!

292
00:15:24.990 --> 00:15:27.240
Hold on! You don't need
to tell them that!

293
00:15:27.240 --> 00:15:28.120
You saw it.

294
00:15:28.120 --> 00:15:30.120
Yeah, but you had an actual reason–

295
00:15:32.330 --> 00:15:36.750
Why did you guys do this
to our mayor?!

296
00:15:36.750 --> 00:15:38.210
Don't give us your excuses!

297
00:15:38.210 --> 00:15:39.420
Who are you?!

298
00:15:39.420 --> 00:15:41.040
Are you with those pirates?!

299
00:15:42.050 --> 00:15:43.760
They're really bloodthirsty...

300
00:15:43.760 --> 00:15:46.510
If we let it slip that
we're thieves or pirates–

301
00:15:46.880 --> 00:15:47.840
We're pirates!

302
00:15:51.260 --> 00:15:52.510
– We thought so!
– We thought so!

303
00:15:54.180 --> 00:15:54.930
You idiot!

304
00:15:54.930 --> 00:15:55.770
It's the truth!

305
00:15:55.770 --> 00:15:56.890
Pirates!

306
00:15:56.890 --> 00:15:59.150
How dare you ravage our town?!

307
00:15:59.150 --> 00:16:01.270
Kids or not, you're in for it!

308
00:16:02.570 --> 00:16:03.650
What now?

309
00:16:03.650 --> 00:16:06.150
Sounds like they won't hear us out.

310
00:16:07.320 --> 00:16:10.120
Run!

311
00:16:11.280 --> 00:16:12.740
There's no escape!

312
00:16:12.740 --> 00:16:16.120
How dare you hurt
our beloved mayor?!

313
00:16:21.210 --> 00:16:23.880
Why did you make things worse?!

314
00:16:23.880 --> 00:16:25.260
This is a good town!

315
00:16:24.590 --> 00:16:25.260
Huh?!

316
00:16:25.710 --> 00:16:29.720
Everyone got so upset
over the old mayor guy!

317
00:16:33.930 --> 00:16:38.060
I bet making excuses
would just make things worse!

318
00:16:38.060 --> 00:16:39.390
We're turning here!

319
00:16:39.390 --> 00:16:42.110
H-Hold on! Give a girl some warning!

320
00:16:42.110 --> 00:16:43.570
They ran into the alley!

321
00:16:48.280 --> 00:16:49.860
Wha...? Chouchou?!

322
00:16:49.860 --> 00:16:51.660
It's the dog!

323
00:16:55.620 --> 00:16:57.830
H-Hey! Move, Chouchou!

324
00:16:57.830 --> 00:16:58.580
Hey!

325
00:16:58.580 --> 00:17:00.210
Those guys are bad pirates!

326
00:17:00.210 --> 00:17:02.000
You're barking at the wrong people!

327
00:17:04.460 --> 00:17:06.670
Why are you getting in the way?!

328
00:17:05.590 --> 00:17:07.590
Chouchou! Let us past!

329
00:17:08.340 --> 00:17:11.930
Later, boy!

330
00:17:20.560 --> 00:17:21.940
That was scary!

331
00:17:21.940 --> 00:17:24.310
We managed to escape
thanks to Chouchou!

332
00:17:24.310 --> 00:17:26.690
Why do we have to put up with this?!

333
00:17:26.690 --> 00:17:28.320
Does it matter now?

334
00:17:28.320 --> 00:17:30.070
We're done here anyway.

335
00:17:30.070 --> 00:17:31.450
Maybe so, but...

336
00:17:31.450 --> 00:17:33.160
Hey, is this your boat?!

337
00:17:33.160 --> 00:17:34.580
It's great!

338
00:17:34.580 --> 00:17:37.660
What's so great about it?

339
00:17:37.660 --> 00:17:39.750
I stole it from some idiot pirates.

340
00:17:39.750 --> 00:17:41.920
That's a big mouth ya got!

341
00:17:43.000 --> 00:17:45.250
Been waitin' for ya, thief girl!

342
00:17:45.250 --> 00:17:47.750
Never thought you'd run
into us here, did you?!

343
00:17:50.010 --> 00:17:51.380
You know them?

344
00:17:51.380 --> 00:17:52.590
Yeah... sort of!

345
00:17:52.590 --> 00:17:56.100
Not sort of! We're bound by fate!

346
00:17:56.100 --> 00:17:57.600
So you had friends, huh?

347
00:17:57.600 --> 00:18:00.480
Guess we'll have to punish you, too!

348
00:18:00.480 --> 00:18:04.520
You'll learn exactly why
you shouldn't steal from others!

349
00:18:04.520 --> 00:18:05.860
Hey, you!

350
00:18:05.860 --> 00:18:10.070
Would you stop
freakin' ignoring me?!

351
00:18:10.070 --> 00:18:11.110
Huh?!

352
00:18:19.910 --> 00:18:22.500
Mayor! Are you conscious?!

353
00:18:24.290 --> 00:18:26.170
Thank goodness! You're all right!

354
00:18:26.170 --> 00:18:27.880
What in the world happened?!

355
00:18:30.340 --> 00:18:31.380
What in the...?!

356
00:18:31.380 --> 00:18:34.050
It was already like this
when we got here!

357
00:18:34.050 --> 00:18:37.930
There were some pirates left,
but they all ran off!

358
00:18:38.930 --> 00:18:41.270
Did you not see anything
that happened?!

359
00:18:41.270 --> 00:18:42.930
Where are those youngsters?!

360
00:18:42.930 --> 00:18:44.140
"Youngsters"?

361
00:18:44.140 --> 00:18:46.270
Do you mean those three kids?

362
00:18:46.860 --> 00:18:49.610
So they're alive?!

363
00:18:50.730 --> 00:18:54.740
Those fools! How dare they harm
a senior citizen like me!

364
00:18:57.070 --> 00:19:00.700
We just finished driving
those idiots away!

365
00:19:00.700 --> 00:19:01.790
But still...!

366
00:19:01.790 --> 00:19:04.790
They almost seemed
to be mocking us!

367
00:19:04.790 --> 00:19:09.590
They'd never understand how we felt
when they attacked our town!

368
00:19:09.590 --> 00:19:11.170
Yeah! Yeah!

369
00:19:11.170 --> 00:19:13.170
Let's catch them before it's too–

370
00:19:13.170 --> 00:19:14.760
Enough of that!

371
00:19:14.760 --> 00:19:17.680
I'm the only one who's
allowed to complain about them!

372
00:19:18.140 --> 00:19:20.970
I won't let anyone else
badmouth them!

373
00:19:20.970 --> 00:19:24.180
Wh-What?! Why are you
protecting pirates?!

374
00:19:24.180 --> 00:19:27.520
Damn them... So they plan
to just disappear?!

375
00:19:27.520 --> 00:19:29.690
Where did they go?!

376
00:19:28.440 --> 00:19:29.690
Huh?

377
00:19:29.690 --> 00:19:31.650
Um... They, uh, ran toward the port.

378
00:19:33.110 --> 00:19:35.110
Damn it!
– Mayor! Mayor!
– Mayor! Mayor!

379
00:19:35.110 --> 00:19:38.410
They think they can do
whatever they please in my town!

380
00:19:38.410 --> 00:19:42.370
I'm gonna give you kids
a piece of my mind!

381
00:19:46.040 --> 00:19:47.790
Alright! Let's get going!

382
00:19:48.710 --> 00:19:52.340
Isn't that Buggy's mark
on your sail there?

383
00:19:52.340 --> 00:19:55.340
Well, this is his boat.
I'll get rid of it soon.

384
00:19:57.220 --> 00:19:58.680
Hey! Wait!

385
00:19:59.090 --> 00:20:01.180
Youngsters!

386
00:20:01.180 --> 00:20:02.640
The old mayor guy!

387
00:20:10.810 --> 00:20:13.440
I was ready to die!

388
00:20:13.440 --> 00:20:17.320
I was ready to die filled with despair!

389
00:20:18.950 --> 00:20:20.780
Thanks! We're in your debt!

390
00:20:24.120 --> 00:20:25.500
Don't worry about it!

391
00:20:25.500 --> 00:20:27.250
Take it easy!

392
00:20:27.660 --> 00:20:29.670
Dammit, kiddos.

393
00:20:29.670 --> 00:20:31.790
Dammit, kiddos!

394
00:20:31.790 --> 00:20:34.420
Dammit, kiddos...

395
00:20:36.260 --> 00:20:38.180
I have no words...

396
00:20:43.100 --> 00:20:44.180
What?

397
00:20:44.180 --> 00:20:46.020
What?!

398
00:20:46.390 --> 00:20:48.440
You left one of the treasure bags?!

399
00:20:48.440 --> 00:20:49.140
Yeah.

400
00:20:49.140 --> 00:20:52.150
I'll have you know just one
is worth five million berries!

401
00:20:52.150 --> 00:20:55.530
But they need money to fix
their destroyed town, right?

402
00:20:55.530 --> 00:20:57.440
That was my treasure!

403
00:20:57.820 --> 00:21:00.410
Do you know what I
went through to steal it?!

404
00:21:01.070 --> 00:21:02.910
Why did you do that?!

405
00:21:02.910 --> 00:21:04.910
Stop! I can't swim!

406
00:21:04.910 --> 00:21:06.660
That's the point!

407
00:21:06.660 --> 00:21:08.540
If you want it,
go back and get it then!

408
00:21:08.540 --> 00:21:10.750
I can't do that! You go get it!

409
00:21:10.750 --> 00:21:13.540
No! That's really dangerous!
I could die, you know!

410
00:21:13.540 --> 00:21:15.210
Then at least die once!

411
00:21:15.750 --> 00:21:18.630
Next time, I'll really
throw you into the ocean!

412
00:21:20.340 --> 00:21:23.390
Well, for better or worse...

413
00:21:23.390 --> 00:21:28.060
looks like we now have a navigator
for the journey ahead.

414
00:21:32.730 --> 00:21:39.590
As a kid, I had a dream of a dazzling treasure

415
00:21:39.790 --> 00:21:46.610
I had a map in my head that I knew would lead me

416
00:21:46.860 --> 00:21:53.710
Charted a course all on my own, so nobody would beat me

417
00:21:53.830 --> 00:22:00.970
The promised land was in my hand, drew a line in the sand

418
00:22:03.670 --> 00:22:06.350
Look where I am

419
00:22:08.580 --> 00:22:14.760
My one ambition's slipping right through my hands

420
00:22:15.100 --> 00:22:22.030
But if the world ever changes I'll call out your name

421
00:22:22.190 --> 00:22:29.110
We could return to a time when our lives were still the same

422
00:22:29.240 --> 00:22:36.240
Take me to the place where memories remain

423
00:22:36.340 --> 00:22:42.110
Please don't ever let them fade
